('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:31d5aad8', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Paso demasiado tiempo en línea’ means…", "options": ["I spend too much time online", "I never go online at all", "I spend only a little time online", "I spend my time offline with friends"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘paso demasiado tiempo en línea’ = I spend too much time online. Every distractor changes the amount or negates it."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:a873b11d', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Higher: ‘Es importante que tengas cuidado’ uses which verb form?", "options": ["the subjunctive (tengas)", "the ordinary present tense (tienes)", "the simple future tense (tendrás)", "a direct command form (ten)"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘es importante que’ triggers the subjunctive: tengas, not tienes."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:feb5c33f', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which describes the safest online habit?", "options": ["proteger la contraseña y no compartir datos personales", "compartir la contraseña con cualquier desconocido que conoces en línea", "publicar todos los datos personales en el perfil", "aceptar como amigo a cualquier desconocido en línea"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Protecting your password and not sharing personal data is safe practice; the others describe risky behaviour."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:903f1ef8', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘the user’?", "options": ["el usuario", "el ordenador", "la aplicación", "la tecnología"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "el usuario = the user. The other three are real tech nouns, but they name a device or concept, not a person."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:0da5a581', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which verb means ‘to comment’?", "options": ["comentar", "compartir", "publicar", "chatear"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "comentar = to comment. compartir (to share), publicar (to post) and chatear (to chat) are all real social-media verbs, but different actions."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:97580a5c', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘emoji’ or ‘emoticon’?", "options": ["el emoticón", "el comentario", "el mensaje", "el perfil"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "el emoticón = emoji/emoticon. comentario (comment), mensaje (message) and perfil (profile) are all real social-media nouns, but different things."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:34b2b2ba', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"Actualizo mi estado con un emoticón divertido.\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. What does the person update?", "options": ["their status, with a fun emoji", "their password, with new letters", "their profile picture only", "their list of followers"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘actualizo mi estado con un emoticón divertido’ = I update my status with a fun emoji. The traps swap in a password, a photo or a follower list."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:9ebdc3db', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which sentence means ‘It’s important to feel safe online’?", "options": ["Es importante sentirte seguro en línea", "Es importante sentirte perdido en línea", "Es importante sentirte solo en línea", "Es importante sentirte triste en línea"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "seguro = safe. perdido (lost), solo (alone) and triste (sad) are real feeling-words that fit the same sentence shape, but change the meaning."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:355ae977', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘safe’?", "options": ["seguro", "peligroso", "divertido", "importante"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "seguro = safe. peligroso (dangerous) is its direct opposite — a very common mix-up; divertido (fun) and importante (important) are unrelated."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:91f348b1', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘consequence’?", "options": ["la consecuencia", "la preocupación", "el peligro", "el impacto"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "la consecuencia = consequence. preocupación (worry), peligro (danger) and impacto (impact) are all similar abstract nouns about risk, easily confused."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:7b0248cd', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which phrase describes ‘the worst mistake’?", "options": ["el peor error", "el mejor error", "el último error", "el mismo error"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "el peor = the worst. el mejor (the best) is the opposite; el último (the last) and el mismo (the same) are other real describing words."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:c03998dd', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘occasion’, as in ‘on one occasion’?", "options": ["la ocasión", "la opción", "la ocupación", "la operación"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "la ocasión = occasion. opción (option), ocupación (occupation) and operación (operation) look similar in writing but mean something different."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety:mcq:8250b67c', 'spanish', 'spanish:8-2-social-media-and-online-safety', '8.2 Social Media and Online Safety', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word means ‘attitude’?", "options": ["la actitud", "la aptitud", "la actividad", "la atención"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "la actitud = attitude. la aptitud (aptitude) is the classic confusable pair; actividad (activity) and atención (attention) look similar too."}'::jsonb),
